@Node "INST" "Installation"

@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

@{b}Installer program installation@{ub}
This installation requires the Installer program.  Using the installer
make the installation a breeze, just double-click on the install icon
and follow the instructions given by the installer.

@EndNode

@Node "WARN" "Important"

@{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}

Due to MIDI communication synchronisation, 05R/W always wait for an
answer from the 05R/W module everytime it sends a SYSEX message, so 
always ensure before running «05R/W» that:

- the 05R/W module is power-on
- MIDI-In and MIDI-Out are connected to the 05R/W module
- SYSEX messages of the 05R/W module are enabled
  (MIDI GLOBAL -> MIDI Filter -> EX:ENA)

@EndNode

@Node "_BNK" "Bank Manager"

@{b}BANK MANAGER@{ub}

This is the main window, it will help you to manage your bank of
programs and combination.  It features:

- move a prog/combi through the bank (list is drag & drop)
- move up, down, top, bottom a prog/combi
- rename a prog/combi
- clear a prog/combi
- load/save a prog/combi from/to disk
- sort the bank in alphabetic order
- import/export from/to 05R/W
- read/write from/to disk

Unregistered users cannot:
- save a prog/combi to disk
- export bank to 05R/W
- write bank to disk

@EndNode

@Node "_CMB" "Combination Editor"

@{b}COMBINATION EDITOR@{ub}

This is were you are going to create some nice combination easily, and
test them in real time. It features:

- a real time test keyboard.

Unregistered users cannot:
- edit Effect1 & Effect2 parameters
- write or rename the combination
- save combination to disk

@EndNode

@Node "_DRM" "Drumkit Editor"

@{b}DRUMKIT EDITOR@{ub}

This window enable you to edit the 2 RAM drumkits. It features:

- dual display of the 2 drumkits 
- complete listview of drumsounds
- test button (space bar) applying on active index
- import/export from/to 05R/W
- read/write from/to disk

Unregistered users cannot:
- edit the key
- export to 05R/W
- write to disk

@EndNode

@Node "_PRG" "Program Editor"

@{b}PROGRAM EDITOR@{ub}

This window is the most interresting part of 05R/W, it allow to edit
a program very easily. It features:

- a real time test keyboard.
- a graphical display of VDA EG, VDF EG and Pitch EG
- a complete listview of multisounds
- grouped pages ordered in 4 catagories:
  · Sound  -> Oscillator, Pitch MG, Frequency, Intensity
  · Filter -> VDF Cutoff, EG, Color, Velocity Sense, Keyboard Tracking 
  · Volume -> VDA EG, Velocity Sense, Keyboard Tracking
  · Main   -> Pitch EG, VDF Modulation, After Touch, Joy Stick Control
  · Effect -> Effect1, Effect2, Placement

Effects specifics parameters by themselves cannot be editing for the moment,
but you must know that every parameter you change directly on the 05R/W
module will be written as well to 05R/W or disk...

Unregistered users cannot:
- edit VDA EG parameters
- edit Effect1 & Effect2 parameters
- edit Pitch EG parameters
- write or rename the program
- save program to disk

@EndNode

@Node "_KBD" "MIDI Keyboard"

@{b}MIDI KEYBOARD@{ub}

This window has been implemented to fast testing your work. It features:

- 05R/W selection (Program, Combi & Banks)
- octave selection of keys
- velocity selection & Hold option
- Quiet button (shut all notes)
- 2 selectable octaves of keys
- realtime controls
  · Control Change (from 1 to 13)
  · After Touch
  · Pitch Bend
- Reset controls button

No restriction for unregistered users.

@EndNode

@Node "HIST" "History"

Version 1.2 (26-Oct-98)
